---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Astro Directory Website Development" description="Astro directory website development for fast, SEO-friendly static architectures with low maintenance overhead.">
  <section class="pt-24 pb-14">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <span class="text-sm text-[#00f0ff] font-['JetBrains_Mono'] tracking-wider">ASTRO BUILD</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mt-4 mb-5 font-['Space_Grotesk']">Astro Directory Website Development</h1>
      <p class="text-[#8b8b9a] text-lg max-w-3xl">Use Astro when you want speed, simplicity, and SEO-friendly static output. Ideal for directory websites that need excellent performance without backend complexity.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-8">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <div class="bg-[#151520] border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-xl p-5"><p class="text-xs text-[#8b8b9a]">Best For</p><p class="text-white mt-1">Static directory builds</p></div>
      <div class="bg-[#151520] border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-xl p-5"><p class="text-xs text-[#8b8b9a]">Performance</p><p class="text-white text-2xl font-['JetBrains_Mono'] mt-1">Sub-second</p></div>
      <div class="bg-[#151520] border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-xl p-5"><p class="text-xs text-[#8b8b9a]">Maintenance</p><p class="text-white mt-1">Low overhead</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-10">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-[#151520] border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-white font-['Space_Grotesk'] mb-4">Astro stack advantages</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-[#c7c7d2]">
          <li>• Lean static output for fast page loads</li>
          <li>• Great base for directory SEO architecture</li>
          <li>• Lower hosting and ops complexity</li>
          <li>• Easier long-term content maintenance</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-[#151520] border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-white font-['Space_Grotesk'] mb-4">When to choose Next.js instead</h2>
        <p class="text-[#8b8b9a]">If you need authentication, user accounts, member dashboards, or heavy backend interactions, Next.js is usually the better path. Use Astro for speed-first static use cases.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-14">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/nextjs-directory-website-development" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-xl">Compare with Next.js</a>
      <a href="/pricing" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-[#0a0a0f] bg-gradient-to-r from-[#00f0ff] to-[#00c8ff] rounded-xl">See packages</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
